{"id": 55826, "date": "2025-01-31T04:00:43", "date_gmt": "2025-01-31T12:00:43", "guid": {"rendered": "https://estreetshuffle.com/?p=55826"}, "modified": "2025-11-19T12:32:08", "modified_gmt": "2025-11-19T20:32:08", "slug": "kingdom-of-days-january-31-2", "status": "publish", "type": "post", "link": "https://estreetshuffle.com/index.php/2025/01/31/kingdom-of-days-january-31-2/", "title": {"rendered": "January 31"}, "content": {"rendered": "<p><strong>1973:</strong> Bruce and the band eventually known as E Street open a six-night, two-shows-nightly stand at Max&#8217;s Kansas City in New York City, opening for Biff Rose. Several tracks from this show are professionally recorded for use on The King Biscuit Flower Hour, but only &#8220;<a href=\"https://estreetshuffle.com/index.php/2021/05/18/roll-of-the-dice-bishop-danced/\">Bishop Danced</a>&#8221; will be aired. That &#8220;Bishop Danced&#8221; recording, however, will see the light of day again 25 years later, when it is released on <em>Tracks</em>.</p>\n<div class=\"jetpack-video-wrapper\"><iframe loading=\"lazy\" title=\"Bishop Danced (Live at Max&#039;s Kansas City - January 1973)\" width=\"758\" height=\"569\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/j3k_B-pvusI?feature=oembed\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share\" referrerpolicy=\"strict-origin-when-cross-origin\" allowfullscreen></iframe></div>\n<div class=\"jetpack-video-wrapper\"><iframe loading=\"lazy\" title=\"New York (1/31/1973)\" width=\"758\" height=\"426\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/videoseries?list=PLu8VBPtfGX1B1rEajyYdvaWwLHODyBt1n\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share\" referrerpolicy=\"strict-origin-when-cross-origin\" allowfullscreen></iframe></div>\n<p>The late show was recorded, too&#8211;but only the first two songs have surfaced. But those songs are ultra&#8211;rare and heard by very few fans in concert: &#8220;Saga of the Architect Angel&#8221; and &#8220;<a href=\"http://estreetshuffle.com/index.php/2019/04/10/roll-of-the-dice-song-for-orphans/\">Song for Orphans</a>.&#8221; Listen to both below.</p>\n<div class=\"jetpack-video-wrapper\"><iframe loading=\"lazy\" title=\"8. Saga Of The Architect Angel (Bruce Springsteen - Live In New York City 1-31-1973)\" width=\"758\" height=\"569\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/L7_6l2W3ybo?feature=oembed\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share\" referrerpolicy=\"strict-origin-when-cross-origin\" allowfullscreen></iframe></div>\n<div class=\"jetpack-video-wrapper\"><iframe loading=\"lazy\" title=\"9. Song To The Orphans (Bruce Springsteen - Live In New York City 1-31-1973)\" width=\"758\" height=\"569\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/voGU6hwjmiw?feature=oembed\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share\" referrerpolicy=\"strict-origin-when-cross-origin\" allowfullscreen></iframe></div>\n<p><strong>1981: </strong>Bruce and the band enjoy their second day off in the Twin Cities (except for Roy, who has an ear infection). Bruce spends the evening playing pool and pinball at a bar called Zoogies, where he catches a local band called The Suburbs.</p>\n<p><strong>1989:</strong>\u00a0<em>Video Anthology 1978-88</em> is released on VHS, the first collection of Bruce&#8217;s music videos.</p>\n<div class=\"jetpack-video-wrapper\"><iframe loading=\"lazy\" title=\"Bruce Springsteen Video Anthology 1978-88\" width=\"758\" height=\"569\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/pWQsmTe_DuU?feature=oembed\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share\" referrerpolicy=\"strict-origin-when-cross-origin\" allowfullscreen></iframe></div>\n<p><img 